			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you are willing to grow the BST to 65.. you get a 65% slow.. that is enough for almost anything.. you can pet tank with even your pet most things.. much less his pet.   A tough pet, good enough slow and Spiritual Dominion.. that's your pro side.  But I am thinking you are a Bard.. you can slow (and play Chorus of Marr if I came to that.. Chorus of Marr &gt; all last time I checked..).
<br />

<br />
Melee positioning is well neigh a full time job.. if DPS is literally your only goal, Mage.. yes.. summoned toys for all your pets and much better nukes than a BST.
<br />

<br />
I am doing the exact setup you are (machine wise).. Necro {main} on one, Cleric and Enchanter on the other (using alt tab).  And, I chain nuke the hell out of Enchanter (and Dire Charm every chance I get).. but there is no way I could manage a melee on top of that (of course I am primary healing and cc and slowing for a full group).
<br />

<br />
Last night was a coasting night for me.. one boxing!   65/190 Necro (me), 65/100 Beastlord and 64/20 Mage doing pet night in Howling Stones.  No fight lasted long enough for me to WTD.. or the Beastlord to melee..mostly because of the Mage chain nuking for 2.5K a pop.. before crits.   But even in longer fights (like Dranik Hollow's), I can always tell when the Mage's Nukes land.
<br />

<br />
Another Mage argument (yes they suck solo) is because they suck solo.. most high end guilds need them.. if that matters.  
<br />

<br />
And do not short change CoTH coupled with fixed length invis.  I know how much fun it can be to move a three character train (oy!) everywhere.. this way you can run one.. and suck the others to you.  I get our Mage to help me all the time in sticky zones.. rather than mess with follow failing and getting us all killed (yet again).
<br />

<br />
So.. assuming your are not using Macroquest to squeeze extra life out of your bot.. I think a Mage will give you more bang for the time you can afford a 3rd session.. send pet, and Nuke as you toggle through.. higher DPS than a Beastlord for the same few keys.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.obsessionmatrix.com/felicite_sig.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
