			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Mortium wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">wait, and forgive my ignorance of macros... pretty sure I've asked this before and most said not that doable
<br />

<br />
can you create macros that launch all your spells/combat actions with one button? for example:
<br />

<br />
/cast 8 (snare)
<br />
/pet attack
<br />
/cast 6 (misc dot)
<br />
/cast 2 (DOT Tap)
<br />
/cast 1 (Tap or Misc DOT)
<br />
/cast 5 (FEAR)
<br />
/sit</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
Not quite.  As someone else said, you have to allow for the pause time between casts.  The good news is you can put a pause on the same line as a cast.
<br />

<br />
/assist MA
<br />
/pet attack
<br />
/cast 3
<br />
/paude 30, /cast 4
<br />
/pause 30, /cast 5
<br />

<br />

<br />
You would have to play around with the pauses a bit but in general this is how you can do it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
