				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am considering a third account as well since groups are much harder to get by nowadays with EQ2 and WoW out among others...
<br />

<br />
I can't seem to imagine how you manage a 65% win rate with your combo since you are lacking some form of a healer.  May not be that hard to find a healer LFG anyways for that third person to start LDON.
<br />

<br />
I would suggest a Ranger for a third account.  
<br />

<br />
-Their regen spells are good enough to offset Lich.
<br />
-Almost Zero Attention.  Gravis Pad/Auto Attack Arrows.
<br />
-2nd or 3rd most damaging class(depending on whose log you look at).
<br />
-Crappy heals but nice to Crit.
<br />

<br />
A BL would be nice as everyone else is suggesting but I imagine being able to control the third character on a gravis pad would be much easier than having to ALT-TAB to the other Account, hitting some hotkeys, compensating those hotkeys for fizzles (so deadly to miss a slow cast on a fizzle), would be alot of work over a 3 hour grind -Versus- ALT TAB, then gravis pad.  No worries about missing a hot key spell cycle due to a fizzled spell.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
